Britain's Food Standards Agency on issued an urgent warning advising people not to eat more than 350 food products inadvertently contaminated with an illegal dye.
The watchdog agency recalled 359 products, ranging from ready-made-meals to a popular brand of instant noodles, after finding traces of the illegal dye Sudan I. Britain's food safety watchdog added another 146 products to a list of items tainted by a potentially cancer-causing dye in the country's largest food recall yet.
